WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:02.683
(upbeat music)

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:15.700
- When using X3, we go higher repetitions

00:00:15.700 --> 00:00:20.498
so the minimum amount of
repetitions you do, should be 15.

00:00:20.498 --> 00:00:22.810
And there's a very good reason for why.

00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:24.620
And it's not a research based reasons

00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:26.033
it's practical based reason.

00:00:26.910 --> 00:00:29.180
Because you're seven times stronger

00:00:29.180 --> 00:00:31.320
in that stronger range out here

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:34.080
than you are back at the bottom.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:37.520
The weight you're using
in that stronger range

00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:41.010
is far beyond what your
one rep maximum would be.

00:00:41.010 --> 00:00:43.960
So like, for example,
when I do the chest press

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:46.160
with this bar and the elite band,

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:50.310
that's the one I use
it's 540 pounds at peak

00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:52.600
and I might do 22 reps.

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:54.880
That's about where I'm at right now.

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:56.803
So do 22 repetitions.

00:00:57.770 --> 00:01:00.930
I'm sure, oh, I couldn't
do a one rep maximum

00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:04.000
on a regular bench press with 540 pounds.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:09.000
So remember X3 is built
to trigger muscle to grow.

00:01:09.630 --> 00:01:13.050
Not so you can talk
about how strong you are.

00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:16.110
If you wanna go do a feat
of strength somewhere else,

00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:19.930
as irresponsible as that
may be, be my guest.

00:01:19.930 --> 00:01:21.550
But that's not what X3 is for.

00:01:21.550 --> 00:01:23.810
So take the ego out of it

00:01:23.810 --> 00:01:26.860
and do 15 repetitions minimum.

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:28.870
Because when you're out here,

00:01:28.870 --> 00:01:31.640
if you can't do at least 15 repetitions

00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:35.170
you're using a weight you
have no business being under

00:01:35.170 --> 00:01:39.160
and you could let go of the
bar and cause an injury.

00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:41.740
You know, it can come and snap
back at you in a chest press

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:43.390
and hit you in the chest.

00:01:43.390 --> 00:01:45.750
It could hit the top of
your feet in a deadlift

00:01:45.750 --> 00:01:47.860
which does happen from time to time.

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:51.030
It doesn't happen to the
people who use it correctly

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:55.500
but it does to the people
who don't use it correctly.

00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:57.233
There's rare exceptions to that.

00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:00.600
One small piece of advice.

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.520
You might not wanna do this
while you're watching your kids

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:04.860
'cause they can distract you

00:02:04.860 --> 00:02:07.730
'cause they are a troublemakers at times.

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:10.430
So, you know, you lose focus

00:02:10.430 --> 00:02:14.340
while you're doing a heavy
weightlifting experience.

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:18.073
You could be distracted
and you could let go.

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:21.330
So, you wanna make sure
you're hanging out at the bar

00:02:21.330 --> 00:02:23.870
15 repetitions minimum.

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:25.740
And then for on the maximum side

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:28.280
we go all the way up to 40 repetitions.

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:31.870
These repetitions are also
very slow and controlled.

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:36.870
Two to three seconds up and
two to three seconds back.

00:02:37.610 --> 00:02:41.010
So that is a very slow
and controlled movement.

00:02:41.010 --> 00:02:45.670
Now, that forces much
more stabilization firing

00:02:45.670 --> 00:02:48.830
which then triggers a
growth hormone regulation.

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:51.870
So this is why people
get so lean so quickly

00:02:51.870 --> 00:02:53.380
using X3.

00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:55.600
So that's really important.

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:57.840
Now what we also see sometimes,

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:02.480
is people saying they wanna do
a light day and a heavy day.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:04.140
Now I know why they wanna do that.

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:07.410
There's a lot of articles
written about periodization.

00:03:07.410 --> 00:03:12.180
Now, periodization does
with regular weightlifting

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:13.810
induce better results.

00:03:13.810 --> 00:03:15.350
The research has shown this

00:03:15.350 --> 00:03:18.100
and the reason why people
do like a light day

00:03:18.100 --> 00:03:21.400
and a heavy day, when
they do periodization

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.920
is 'cause you kinda build
up, you go light days

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:25.610
and the medium days and the heavy days

00:03:25.610 --> 00:03:28.290
and then you kinda cycle back down.

00:03:28.290 --> 00:03:31.840
The reason is, you're focused
more on sarcoplasmic growth,

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:34.670
which is the volume of a cell

00:03:34.670 --> 00:03:36.740
with a sarcoplasmic type stimulus.

00:03:36.740 --> 00:03:39.320
And that's a high repetition type day.

00:03:39.320 --> 00:03:44.320
And on a lower repetition heavier day,

00:03:45.490 --> 00:03:48.960
the quote heavy days,
you're using a higher weight

00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:52.410
to try and stimulate myofibril growth,

00:03:52.410 --> 00:03:55.350
which is actually the density of the cell,

00:03:55.350 --> 00:03:58.190
as opposed to just the
volume, the density and power.

00:03:58.190 --> 00:04:00.540
So, they compliment each other.

00:04:00.540 --> 00:04:05.100
But with weights, you can't
get both in one experience.

00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:10.100
Now, applying this 2X3, is not smart.

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:15.810
Because every experience with X3,

00:04:15.810 --> 00:04:18.390
is the benefit of a heavy day.

00:04:18.390 --> 00:04:21.280
And it is the benefit of a light day.

00:04:21.280 --> 00:04:23.710
So you get both at once.

00:04:23.710 --> 00:04:25.280
So the benefit of the heavy day

00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:30.040
is when you are going to
fatigue in this range of motion

00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:34.240
and using a weight
beyond a one rep maximum.

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:37.830
So you're triggering all kinds of growth,

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:39.830
well first fatigue and then growth.

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:42.750
And then as you diminish the range,

00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:45.610
because this is a very
important part of the protocol

00:04:45.610 --> 00:04:50.610
as you can't get to that stronger range

00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:53.250
you do shorter repetitions.

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:56.603
So my last few repetitions
in the chest press,

00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:00.910
like, let's say half in my
last, let's say two or three

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:02.750
might only be like one inch.

00:05:02.750 --> 00:05:04.750
Now when that happens

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:10.070
you're evacuating all of the ATP glycogen

00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:12.770
and creating phosphate in the cells,

00:05:12.770 --> 00:05:16.570
forcing the cells to get rid
of all of their contract fuels

00:05:16.570 --> 00:05:18.250
which then volumize the cell.

00:05:18.250 --> 00:05:21.710
So you get the benefit of both

00:05:21.710 --> 00:05:23.813
in every experience with X3.

